textBeforeTable: The Three Lions, who suffered a difficult first day, reached stumps on 302-5 as the batsmen found their groove. England smashed through the Australian lower order to set themselves a first innings target of 304, a number they are likely to pass within the first over of the third day. England trail an Australia Invitational XI by two runs with five wickets remaining at the close of play on the second day in Sydney. However, things changed quickly after the restart, the Englishman racking up three wickets in quick succession to take his overall to five. Peter Nevill and Joshua Laylor fell to Finn before Boyd Rankin took his first wicket of the match when he dismissed Christopher Tremain.
